highlights.description: Yes, this has been a consideration from the very beginning and I'm glad to see it being brought up by the participants in conversations. We'd love feedback and ideas on how we can do a better job of raising awareness and interest across ALL of Madison about LVN!
I love that Madison is the kind of place where LVN conversations happen
KC: This person says I have made an effort to connect with people unlike myself. Would be good to play in a group of white residents who are lamenting their lack of interaction with people of color.
A formative moment of hearing the story of a person experiencing homelessness
Should people be compensated for sharing their story
Story about eating off a charger, teaching a lesson that we should not expect people to join an unfamiliar context and automatically succeed
What has to happen for talk to lead to action?
Example of story of personal experience leading to productive conversation
